Package: updog
Type: Package
Title: Using Parental Data for Offspring Genotyping
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("David", "Gerard", email = "dcgerard@uchicago.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements a Bayesian approach to estimating the genotype
    of offspring given both their sequence data and the sequence data from
    their parents. This package works for species of any ploidy.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/dcgerard/updog
BugReports: http://github.com/dcgerard/updog/issues
Suggests:
    testthat,
    covr,
    ggplot2,
    VGAM,
    txtplot
Imports:
    assertthat
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
